93
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:29,840
Speaker 15: And that's not mentioning

94
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:30,700
Speaker 8: sabotage.

95
00:05:31,260 --> 00:05:33,540
Speaker 5: But it wasn't really an explosion, was it?

96
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:35,260
Speaker 5: It just disappeared.

97
00:05:36,260 --> 00:05:40,200
Speaker 8: In all probability, they were swallowed by a Dirac-C, just as Unit 1 was.

98
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:42,440
Speaker 8: Then the restored S-2 engine is...

99
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:42,920
Speaker 8: Gone.

100
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:44,740
Speaker 8: Along with our hopes.

101
00:05:45,060 --> 00:05:47,020
Speaker 8: We're being forced to use things we don't understand.

102
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:48,200
Speaker 8: Yes.

103
00:05:48,980 --> 00:05:49,820
Speaker 8: Things like the Avis.

104
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:53,520
Speaker 8: So what'll we do with Unit 3?

105
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:55,620
Speaker 8: It's being shipped here as we speak.

106
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,960
Speaker 8: The U.S. government doesn't want to risk losing their first branch as well.

107
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:02,400
Speaker 8: Didn't they insist on the right to build Units 3 and 4 in the first place?

108
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:04,240
Speaker 8: And now they're forcing it off on us?

109
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:05,740
Speaker 8: They're really pushing it.

110
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:07,900
Speaker 8: Well, you can't blame them, can you?

111
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:10,860
Speaker 8: After a disaster like that, anyone would get nervous.

112
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:12,160
Speaker 8: We'll handle it.

113
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,400
Speaker 8: And how are you going to handle the test activation?

114
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:16,280
Speaker 8: Will you use Ray's dummy plug?

115
00:06:17,380 --> 00:06:18,240
Speaker 8: I'll decide soon.

116
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:27,920
Speaker 8: This is the dummy plug prototype. Ray's personal data has been transferred into it, but our current technology can't really digitize a human mind and soul.

117
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:35,220
Speaker 8: In the end, this is nothing but a pale duplication that emulates the real pilot's thinking processes. It's still only a machine.

118
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:42,500
