119
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:44,880
Speaker 7: Load the data into units one and two.

120
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:47,840
Speaker 8: But we're still working out the bugs, sir.

121
00:06:48,060 --> 00:06:49,720
Speaker 7: Just do it. It's sufficient.

122
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:50,880
Speaker 8: Yes, sir.

123
00:06:54,620 --> 00:06:56,880
Speaker 7: I've delegated the transport of the unit to the UN.

124
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:59,080
Speaker 7: It will be here by the end of the weekend.

125
00:06:59,540 --> 00:07:01,400
Speaker 7: At that time, you will take care of it.

126
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:05,140
Speaker 8: Yes, sir. We'll perform the modifications and activation test in Matsushiro.

127
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:07,100
Speaker 7: Hmm. And the test pilot?

128
00:07:07,740 --> 00:07:09,540
Speaker 8: Use of the dummy plug is not recommended.

129
00:07:10,020 --> 00:07:11,100
Speaker 8: One of our candidates...

130
00:07:11,140 --> 00:07:12,720
Speaker 7: Will be chosen as the fourth.

131
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:16,800
Speaker 8: Yes, sir. There is one child available whose core can be prepared immediately.

132
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:18,880
Speaker 7: Then make it so.

133
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:19,540
Speaker 8: Yes, sir.

134
